decade at the Kennedy School

00:04:09.720 --> 00:04:12.630
working to build the
teaching and learning unit

00:04:12.630 --> 00:04:15.180
over there, the SLATE
program and the Case program.

00:04:15.180 --> 00:04:18.149
And I think the Kennedy School
invested incredibly heavily

00:04:18.149 --> 00:04:22.440
in supporting faculty to teach
in a broad array of ways.

00:04:22.440 --> 00:04:24.480
It's very heterogeneous
curriculum.

00:04:24.480 --> 00:04:27.150
And I think they
had a lot of success

00:04:27.150 --> 00:04:29.840
in the elective curriculum
on an opt-in basis.

00:04:29.840 --> 00:04:31.714
So individual
faculty working alone

00:04:31.714 --> 00:04:33.880
in their classrooms in their
elective courses, which

00:04:33.880 --> 00:04:37.080
constitute about 90% of
their course offerings,

00:04:37.080 --> 00:04:39.900
chose to engage with this
incredible array of resources

00:04:39.900 --> 00:04:40.680
that we provided.

00:04:40.680 --> 00:04:44.390
But it Was a little bit tougher
to get really meaningful change

00:04:44.390 --> 00:04:46.770
in the core curriculum.

00:04:46.770 --> 00:04:49.130
So now having recently--
very recently-- joined

00:04:49.130 --> 00:04:52.440
the medical school,
one of the reasons

00:04:52.440 --> 00:04:54.750
that I chose to make
that move is I'm

00:04:54.750 --> 00:04:57.540
really interested
in working at scale.

00:04:57.540 --> 00:04:59.700
And the medical
school has decided

00:04:59.700 --> 00:05:03.370
to do what I would describe as
a big bang change to the way

00:05:03.370 --> 00:05:04.890
that they're teaching.

00:05:04.890 --> 00:05:08.130
So it's not just individual
faculty opting in.

00:05:08.130 --> 00:05:11.610
It was faculty working
together to define what

00:05:11.610 --> 00:05:14.880
should our graduates
know and be able to do

00:05:14.880 --> 00:05:17.280
at the end of four years
at Harvard Medical School.

00:05:17.280 --> 00:05:18.870
And they basically
worked backwards

00:05:18.870 --> 00:05:21.450
to redesign
competencies, courses,

00:05:21.450 --> 00:05:24.540
and even change the pedagogy
across the board with a much

00:05:24.540 --> 00:05:27.120
larger faculty than
the Kennedy School has.

00:05:27.120 --> 00:05:30.327
And so for me, that was
a really inspiring move,

00:05:30.327 --> 00:05:32.910
and I joined the team to try to
figure out how did they do it?

00:05:32.910 --> 00:05:34.744
How do you make it successful?

00:05:34.744 --> 00:05:36.160
And is there
anything there that's

00:05:36.160 --> 00:05:38.040
replicable for other
parts of Harvard

00:05:38.040 --> 00:05:39.550
or other parts of higher ed.

00:05:39.550 --> 00:05:42.160
So that's kind of the
lens that I'm bringing.

00:05:42.160 --> 00:05:42.780
Great.

