an interesting discussion

00:24:14.250 --> 00:24:16.240
as the spectrum of offerings.

00:24:16.240 --> 00:24:18.402
So we had the business school.

00:24:18.402 --> 00:24:20.110
I'm from the business
school, and Nancy's

00:24:20.110 --> 00:24:21.526
from the business
school, where we

00:24:21.526 --> 00:24:24.360
have I think the
most significantly

00:24:24.360 --> 00:24:27.220
hands-on new teacher training.

00:24:27.220 --> 00:24:31.080
So we have a three
day compulsory program

00:24:31.080 --> 00:24:35.430
for new faculty to come through
where they observe classes

00:24:35.430 --> 00:24:37.760
being taught to
them as students,

00:24:37.760 --> 00:24:42.000
they teach to themselves
and they get feedback on it,

00:24:42.000 --> 00:24:44.460
and then are introduced to
the Christensen Center, which

00:24:44.460 --> 00:24:49.770
is a administration
supported and funded

00:24:49.770 --> 00:24:54.370
voluntary group of five
people who are purely there

00:24:54.370 --> 00:24:56.810
for their teaching development.

00:24:56.810 --> 00:24:59.530
To the opposite end of the
spectrum at the law school,

00:24:59.530 --> 00:25:01.500
where they're given a
mentor when they come in,

00:25:01.500 --> 00:25:05.370
but it's more self-forming
groups around academic interest

00:25:05.370 --> 00:25:09.270
areas and research
areas where they kind of

00:25:09.270 --> 00:25:12.120
get together and talk about the
teaching of that little moment.

00:25:12.120 --> 00:25:13.661
And it's not that
it's not happening,

00:25:13.661 --> 00:25:14.790
but it's more informal.

00:25:14.790 --> 00:25:18.030
So the question is
whose responsibility

00:25:18.030 --> 00:25:19.880
is teaching excellence, then?

00:25:19.880 --> 00:25:25.500
Is it administrative, as a
school and as a department,

00:25:25.500 --> 00:25:27.450
that we will set
these things in motion

00:25:27.450 --> 00:25:31.480
and give them financial support
and administrative support?

00:25:31.480 --> 00:25:32.421
Or is it the faculty?

00:25:32.421 --> 00:25:33.795
So one of the
things I shared was

00:25:33.795 --> 00:25:36.910
when the Christensen Center
was first established,

00:25:36.910 --> 00:25:39.400
there was questioning
amongst the faculty

00:25:39.400 --> 00:25:43.230
that a center like that
would allow and give

00:25:43.230 --> 00:25:47.550
a pass to a tenured faculty
to miss their mentoring

00:25:47.550 --> 00:25:52.592
opportunities and basically
abdicate their responsibility

00:25:52.592 --> 00:25:55.220
to the junior faculty.

00:25:55.220 --> 00:25:59.050
To not have to take part
in that process of teaching

00:25:59.050 --> 00:26:02.260
junior faculty because somebody
else is going to do it.

00:26:02.260 --> 00:26:07.020
And that they don't-- that the
burden is off the shoulders

00:26:07.020 --> 00:26:10.890
of the senior faculty, but
that their voices are just

00:26:10.890 --> 00:26:11.670
as important.

00:26:11.670 --> 00:26:17.010
So as a center, we learned
early to make those voices come

00:26:17.010 --> 00:26:19.030
into the work of the center.

00:26:19.030 --> 00:26:20.220
And how do we keep that.

00:26:20.220 --> 00:26:22.680
But that is then our
administrative department's

00:26:22.680 --> 00:26:26.790
burden of maintaining
that ecosystem.

00:26:26.790 --> 00:26:29.620
So it becomes its own beast.

00:26:29.620 --> 00:26:34.800
And the third leg to the
stool then is from the library

00:26:34.800 --> 00:26:36.530
